1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:02,767
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:05,833 --> 00:00:06,967
The detonation switch.

3
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:08,100
Sir Aldrin took it.

4
00:00:08,233 --> 00:00:10,167
Why don't we finish them now?

5
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:12,667
We shoot them in the legs first

6
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,000
then we blow the place up.

7
00:00:15,133 --> 00:00:17,500
We'll all explode here together!

8
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:19,300
- [GUN FIRES]
- Mom!

9
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:21,633
- Mom!
- You ruined my life!

10
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:22,967
You're a demon!

11
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:24,567
[GRUNTING]

12
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,567
You're next after your mother!

13
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,167
I'll finish you!

14
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:37,567
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

15
00:01:18,267 --> 00:01:20,600
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

16
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:22,067
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

17
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:24,333
What do you think is happening
to mom and grandmother?

18
00:01:24,467 --> 00:01:25,400
I really hope they are okay.

19
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:27,200
I hope they get rescued soon.

20
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:31,033
Could mom be with the people
who took them?

21
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:32,500
What are we waiting for?

22
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,800
Why don't we finish them
already?

23
00:01:34,933 --> 00:01:38,700
We're not killing them yet,
Thea.

24
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:39,733
What?

25
00:01:39,867 --> 00:01:41,667
What do you mean?

26
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:44,933
Aunt Thea has been consumed
by anger and bitterness.

27
00:01:45,067 --> 00:01:47,433
I don't think
you can change your mind.

28
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:52,800
We shoot them in the legs first
so they can't walk.

29
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:56,300
Then once we're out
of this building,

30
00:01:56,433 --> 00:01:58,833
we blow it up.

31
00:01:58,967 --> 00:02:01,633
I'm so sorry.

32
00:02:01,767 --> 00:02:04,700
I'm sorry for what mom did
to grandmother and Aunt Marj.

33
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,767
I'm really sorry, I'm so sorry.

34
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:08,733
Ashley, don't apologize.

35
00:02:08,867 --> 00:02:10,767
You didn't want this to happen.

36
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:13,700
You're not responsible
for your mom's actions.

37
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:16,100
That's right, good thing
you didn't turn out like her.

38
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:19,767
Let's just pray that nothing bad
happens to grandmother and mom.

39
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:23,367
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:02:25,467 --> 00:02:27,800
- [GRUNTS]
- [REGINA EXCLAIMS]

41
00:02:27,933 --> 00:02:29,600
That way,

42
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:33,667
Marj and Regina will see
the building collapse

43
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:34,767
with them inside.

44
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:39,400
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:02:39,533 --> 00:02:40,767
[MARJ EXCLAIMS]

46
00:02:42,733 --> 00:02:44,133
Exciting.

47
00:02:44,267 --> 00:02:45,600
I love it!

48
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:52,300
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

49
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:55,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:58,067
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

51
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:01,100
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

52
00:03:04,867 --> 00:03:07,100
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:22,333
Damn it!

54
00:03:22,467 --> 00:03:24,033
How did they find us?

55
00:03:24,167 --> 00:03:26,033
[ALDRIN EXCLAIMS]

56
00:03:26,167 --> 00:03:27,967
Why are you scared?

57
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:30,533
Weren't you all so brave,
so arrogant?

58
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:32,833
So what now?
Your plan is ruined?

59
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:35,633
If I were you, surrender now
and let us go

60
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:38,233
so there will be fewer charges
filed against you!

61
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:40,200
Shut up!

62
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:43,300
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:49,200
Dad, please stay here.

64
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:52,033
You're still weak,
you might get hurt.

65
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:54,267
But I want to help!

66
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:55,933
Dad, I promise you,

67
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:58,300
I'll rescue mom and Marj.

68
00:03:58,433 --> 00:04:00,933
Just stay here
and please listen to me,

69
00:04:01,067 --> 00:04:02,200
where you'll be safer.

70
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:04,933
Just make sure, my child,
you bring them back to us.

71
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:08,200
Let's go, Mr. Torrecampo.

72
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:11,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:04:16,633 --> 00:04:17,833
[GRUNTING]

74
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:19,600
- Call a medic!
- Okay, Sir.

75
00:04:19,733 --> 00:04:20,967
Who did this?

76
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:23,167
Sir Aldrin did it, Sir.

77
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:25,067
[THUMPS]

78
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:28,733
Sir, the detonation switch
was taken by Sir Aldrin.

79
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:30,333
Detonation switch?

80
00:04:30,467 --> 00:04:32,300
Does that mean
there are bombs here?

81
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,533
No!

82
00:04:34,667 --> 00:04:36,900
I won't allow us to be arrested!

83
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:39,900
I won't allow everything
we planned to be destroyed!

84
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:41,133
Me neither!

85
00:04:41,267 --> 00:04:43,033
I don't want to go to jail!

86
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:46,033
I'd rather die
than go to prison!

87
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:49,767
Sir, this building is scheduled
for controlled demolition.

88
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:53,800
There are planted explosives
throughout the building.

89
00:04:53,933 --> 00:04:58,067
Aldrin's plan now is to bury
my mother and spouse alive.

90
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,267
Sir, we need to go to them.

91
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,500
We're out of time,
we have to stop Aldrin.

92
00:05:01,667 --> 00:05:03,433
It's too dangerous,
I'll call SWAT.

93
00:05:03,567 --> 00:05:04,900
Sir, there's no time!

94
00:05:05,033 --> 00:05:07,167
My mother's life and my spouse's
life are at stake!

95
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:08,800
Mr. Torrecampo, come back!

96
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:09,833
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:05:09,967 --> 00:05:11,033
Medic! Medic!

98
00:05:11,167 --> 00:05:12,367
Medic, double time!

99
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:16,267
Men, follow Mr. Torrecampo!

100
00:05:18,567 --> 00:05:20,933
Sir, help is on the way.

101
00:05:21,067 --> 00:05:25,133
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:05:25,267 --> 00:05:27,133
Aldrin, what do we do now?

103
00:05:27,267 --> 00:05:29,867
How do we escape the police?

104
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,967
Do something!

105
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,267
Shut up!

106
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:35,067
How can I think
if you keep talking?

107
00:05:35,233 --> 00:05:37,100
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:38,167
[SQUEALS]

109
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:41,500
- Let go of me!
- You deserve to...

110
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:43,600
Regina, stop!

111
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:44,733
Regina!

112
00:05:44,867 --> 00:05:47,833
- [THUDS]
- [CLAMORING]

113
00:05:50,467 --> 00:05:52,167
[SLAPS]

114
00:05:54,033 --> 00:05:55,067
[THUDS]

115
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,700
[GRUNTS]

116
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:59,067
[CLAMORING]

117
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,767
Go on, shoot!

118
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:02,367
I'll press this!

119
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:06,533
I'll make sure we all die
together and get buried here!

120
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:09,567
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

121
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,567
Let go of mom, Thea!

122
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:15,100
I swear!

123
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:16,833
We'll all die here together!

124
00:06:16,967 --> 00:06:18,867
Don't test me!

125
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,100
- Mom, come here!
- Give it to me, Marj.

126
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:26,567
[EXCLAIMS]

127
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,267
Give it to me, Marj!

128
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,100
You're just dragging this out!

129
00:06:30,233 --> 00:06:32,567
The ending will be the same.

130
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:35,533
You'll both die!

131
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:39,333
Don't test me because we'll all
explode here together!

132
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:40,733
Try me!

133
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:44,767
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

134
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:47,133
Mom, run!

135
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:49,967
Let's chase them!

136
00:06:52,233 --> 00:06:55,500
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

137
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:00,067
Where are those animals?

138
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,700
They disappeared so fast.

139
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:07,200
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

140
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,267
What? Where are we now?

141
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:12,367
This way.

142
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,400
Let's go.

143
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:17,933
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:22,033
Police!

145
00:07:22,167 --> 00:07:24,433
Put your guns down!

146
00:07:24,567 --> 00:07:26,300
You animal!

147
00:07:26,433 --> 00:07:28,200
Where are mom and Marj?

148
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:31,000
Surrender now if you don't want
to rot in jail!

149
00:07:31,133 --> 00:07:34,267
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,100
Even until death,

151
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:38,133
we will never surrender!

152
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:39,800
[GUN FIRES]

153
00:07:39,933 --> 00:07:41,933
[GUN FIRING]

154
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:47,467
[GUN FIRING]

155
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,800
Move! Move! Move!

156
00:07:48,967 --> 00:07:52,333
[GUN FIRING]

157
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,967
[GUN FIRING]

158
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:05,567
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:08,233
What do we do now?

160
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:10,133
I don't want to rot in jail!

161
00:08:10,267 --> 00:08:11,300
Go ahead, Thea.

162
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:13,267
I'll handle the police.

163
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:15,433
Find Marj and Regina.

164
00:08:15,567 --> 00:08:16,500
Kill them already!

165
00:08:16,633 --> 00:08:17,900
But, Aldrin!

166
00:08:18,033 --> 00:08:20,367
They can't escape!

167
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,600
Hurry up!

168
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:24,033
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,500
[GUN FIRING]

170
00:08:31,133 --> 00:08:33,233
[GUN FIRING]

171
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:41,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:52,000
Mom! Mom!

173
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:53,633
- [COUGHING]
- Are you okay?

174
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:58,300
Marj, whatever happens to me,

175
00:08:58,433 --> 00:08:59,933
promise me this, okay?

176
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:03,767
Don't stop until Thea
is punished for killing Edward.

177
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:04,867
Promise me!

178
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,300
Mom, don't say that!

179
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:08,433
We'll get out of here!

180
00:09:08,567 --> 00:09:10,133
Paolo and the police are here.

181
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:12,067
They'll help us.

182
00:09:13,267 --> 00:09:17,167
Marj, I wish I could
turn back time.

183
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:21,833
I wish I had loved you
and accepted you before.

184
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:24,633
So if I never said it,

185
00:09:24,767 --> 00:09:27,067
I'm sorry for everything.
[SOBBING]

186
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,067
Mom, please.

187
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:33,000
We'll be okay, we'll talk
about this at home.

188
00:09:33,133 --> 00:09:34,767
- Okay.
- Come on, we need to leave now.

189
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:36,033
Okay.

190
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:39,467
[GUN FIRES]

191
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:43,467
Mom!

192
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,567
Mom!

193
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,633
Marj...

194
00:09:46,767 --> 00:09:47,733
Mom!

195
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:54,667
Mom! Mom!

196
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,667
Mom!

197
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,267
Mom!

198
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,133
Mom!

199
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:02,767
Mom!

200
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:06,733
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:08,133
Mom!

202
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:10,200
<i> Mom, wake up!</i>

203
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,700
<i> Mom!</i>

204
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,900
Stop pretending, Marj.

205
00:10:14,033 --> 00:10:16,100
Why are you crying
over that woman?

206
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:19,133
She made your life miserable
for many years.

207
00:10:19,267 --> 00:10:21,433
You're a real demon!

208
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:24,333
You're just adding more charges
to your crimes.

209
00:10:24,467 --> 00:10:27,100
Prison isn't enough for you,
you deserve to die!

210
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,867
[GRUMBLING]

211
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,767
[GUN FIRING]

212
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:40,267
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

213
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,200
[THUDDING]

214
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:47,333
- [INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GUN FIRES]

215
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,600
You animal!

216
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,000
[EXCLAIMS]

217
00:10:52,133 --> 00:10:54,500
[CLAMORING]

218
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:58,167
You animal! You demon!

219
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:01,033
[SLAPS]

220
00:11:02,433 --> 00:11:04,067
You animal!

221
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,567
This is all your fault!

222
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:07,767
You ruined my life!

223
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,200
You animal!

224
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,733
I'll kill you!

225
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:13,367
[CLAMORING]

226
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:20,700
Thea, have mercy!

227
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:22,700
Have mercy on your child!

228
00:11:24,133 --> 00:11:26,333
She's just like Edward!

229
00:11:26,467 --> 00:11:29,000
She never truly loved me!

230
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,833
She just ignored me!

231
00:11:30,967 --> 00:11:33,367
[SOBBING]

232
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:36,333
That's why I don't care
about her anymore.

233
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:38,433
Be together in death!

234
00:11:38,567 --> 00:11:39,767
Die already!

235
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:42,567
[GRUNTING]

236
00:11:44,733 --> 00:11:45,967
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

237
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:48,700
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

238
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:04,567
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

239
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:05,767
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

240
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:08,200
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

241
00:12:19,433 --> 00:12:20,900
Die already!

242
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:24,333
You're nothing compared to me!

243
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:25,900
I'll finish you!

244
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:27,700
You're next after your mother!

245
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:29,733
I'll kill you!

246
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:32,367
[PAOLO SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

247
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:34,167
Mom, it's Paolo!

248
00:12:35,967 --> 00:12:38,467
Marj, go to Paolo now.

249
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,600
I can handle myself,
I'll take care of it.

250
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:42,500
Mom, you can't, you're injured.

251
00:12:42,633 --> 00:12:44,867
Marj, I've already lost
one child.

252
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,033
I can't handle it
if I lose Paolo too.

253
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:48,933
Go on, go to him now.

254
00:12:50,067 --> 00:12:51,867
Go!

255
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,867
Save my child, go now!

256
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:58,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:13:08,633 --> 00:13:09,633
[THUDS]

258
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,800
[THUDDING]

259
00:13:18,933 --> 00:13:20,967
- [GUN FIRES]
- [EXCLAIMS]

260
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:25,033
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

261
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,500
Help!

262
00:13:36,933 --> 00:13:38,200
Help!

263
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:41,300
My child and my daughter-in-law
are upstairs with that Thea.

264
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:42,400
Please, help them.

265
00:13:42,533 --> 00:13:43,933
Yes, Ma'am, let's go help them.

266
00:13:44,067 --> 00:13:46,500
- Come on, come on.
- Hurry, move faster.

267
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:50,833
<i> Greg!</i>

268
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:55,200
Greg!

269
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:57,433
Regina!

270
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:59,800
Greg!

271
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:01,700
Greg!
[SOBBING]

272
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:04,600
Greg!

273
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:07,600
Are you hurt?

274
00:14:07,733 --> 00:14:09,333
No, it's just a graze.

275
00:14:09,467 --> 00:14:11,933
[SOBBING]

276
00:14:13,133 --> 00:14:16,833
Thank God you're safe.

277
00:14:16,967 --> 00:14:19,033
I was so worried about you.

278
00:14:19,167 --> 00:14:22,700
I thought we'd never
see each other again.

279
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:28,767
[SOBBING]

280
00:14:28,933 --> 00:14:32,067
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

281
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:37,467
Where are Paolo and Marj?

282
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:39,467
Love, I'm sorry,
I left your mom behind.

283
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,567
I had no choice.

284
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:42,233
I couldn't leave you.

285
00:14:42,367 --> 00:14:43,367
It's okay.

286
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,600
- Where's my mom?
- Your mom is safe now.

287
00:14:45,733 --> 00:14:48,000
The medics are taking care
of her.

288
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:49,967
Where are the suspects now?

289
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:51,933
Aldrin Castelo.

290
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:53,933
I shot him in self-defense.

291
00:14:54,067 --> 00:14:58,067
Thea is on the sixth floor,
she lost consciousness.

292
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,000
Go on! Take her downstairs.

293
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:01,333
I'll handle this here.

294
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:16,000
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

295
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,200
[GRUNTING]

296
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:29,100
[PANTING]

297
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:35,000
[GRUNTING]

298
00:15:38,867 --> 00:15:44,067
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

299
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:49,433
[EXCLAIMS]

300
00:15:49,567 --> 00:15:54,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

301
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:57,867
Sir.

302
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,733
Here's the switch
for the building explosives.

303
00:16:00,867 --> 00:16:02,367
Please, keep it safe.

304
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,667
Yes, Ma'am.

305
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:08,033
To hell with you, Marj!

306
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:10,233
If I'm going to jail anyway,

307
00:16:10,367 --> 00:16:13,567
I'll make sure I kill you first!

308
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,267
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

309
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,433
[GUN FIRES]

310
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:22,400
[THUDS]

311
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:23,967
Marj!

312
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,000
Run! The building
is going to explode!

313
00:16:26,133 --> 00:16:28,167
- Come on!
- Wait, Thea!

314
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:29,633
It's too late!
Think about the kids!

315
00:16:29,767 --> 00:16:31,733
- Come on!
- Run!

316
00:16:31,867 --> 00:16:35,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:16:47,233 --> 00:16:49,533
[LOUD EXPLOSION]

318
00:16:55,333 --> 00:16:57,333
[LOUD EXPLOSION]

319
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:07,433
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:17:07,567 --> 00:17:11,933
So, this is...

321
00:17:12,067 --> 00:17:16,233
where everything ends.

322
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,933
But...
[PANTING]

323
00:17:19,067 --> 00:17:20,600
I still win.

324
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:23,667
Because...

325
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:27,867
they won't catch me.

326
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:36,067
They'll never put me in jail.
[PANTING]

327
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,600
[LOUD EXPLOSION]

328
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,833
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

329
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:00,333
- Thank God you're safe.
- Mommy!

330
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:01,533
Careful, Jasmine.

331
00:18:01,667 --> 00:18:03,333
Your mom has injuries.

332
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:05,067
Daddy!

333
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,800
I'm okay.

334
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:09,167
We saw what happened
on the news.

335
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,467
Are you all right?

336
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,467
Yeah, yeah, I'm okay, my child.

337
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,533
I promise.

338
00:18:13,767 --> 00:18:15,167
Where's grandmother?

339
00:18:19,467 --> 00:18:20,733
She's in the hospital.

340
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:21,933
She's injured.

341
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,733
But she'll be okay.

342
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:26,433
We'll just get a few things.

343
00:18:26,567 --> 00:18:30,000
Then your dad and I
will go back to her.

344
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:32,367
Poor Ma'am Regina.

345
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,733
I hope she'll be okay.

346
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:37,467
We'll visit her tomorrow, Sir.

347
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:40,133
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

348
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:45,667
What about mom?

349
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,133
If she's not here,

350
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:49,433
then did the police
already catch her?

351
00:18:49,567 --> 00:18:51,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

352
00:18:59,933 --> 00:19:02,433
Your mom...

353
00:19:02,567 --> 00:19:04,967
she wasn't arrested
by the police.

354
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:11,767
<i>I don't care anymore
what Ashley thinks!</i>

355
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:14,100
<i> Even if she hates me for it!</i>

356
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:17,033
<i>She prefers you anyway,
doesn't she?</i>

357
00:19:17,167 --> 00:19:19,800
<i> Fine, then stay together!</i>

358
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:21,600
<i>I don't care about her anymore!</i>

359
00:19:21,733 --> 00:19:23,467
<i> She's just a burden to me!</i>

360
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:27,267
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

361
00:19:29,167 --> 00:19:32,667
Your mom apologized to me.

362
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,700
Not just to us,

363
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:36,267
but also to you.

364
00:19:39,133 --> 00:19:44,233
She told me she hopes
you can forgive her.

365
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:48,900
Because that was the most
important thing to her.

366
00:19:49,033 --> 00:19:50,467
And you,

367
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:53,067
you are very important to her.

368
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:57,233
Your mom loves you very much,
Ashley.

369
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:00,467
She told me that if...

370
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:03,700
if only she could
turn back time,

371
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:06,200
she would.

372
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:09,433
So you and your dad
could start over again.

373
00:20:09,567 --> 00:20:11,733
She wanted to make things right
with your dad.

374
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,500
So...

375
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:17,867
she helped us escape,

376
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:21,233
your Aunt Marj
and your grandmother,

377
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,767
from the collapsing building.

378
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,300
But...

379
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:31,067
it was too late for her.

380
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:34,533
She didn't make it.

381
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:37,400
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

382
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,733
No.

383
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:43,000
No, no!

384
00:20:43,133 --> 00:20:44,333
No, no!

385
00:20:44,467 --> 00:20:46,767
No!
[SOBBING]

386
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,833
No! No!

387
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:55,833
No!
[SOBBING]

388
00:20:55,967 --> 00:20:56,567
I can't...

389
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:59,833
I can't be alone, Aunt Marj.

390
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:03,533
My child, listen to me.

391
00:21:03,667 --> 00:21:07,933
Your mom made a sacrifice
to earn your forgiveness.

392
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:12,433
So there would still be someone
who will love and care for you.

393
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:16,433
Someone who won't just run away
or hide.

394
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,200
Someone who will always be there
for you.

395
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:24,133
You are not alone, Ashley.

396
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:26,567
We're here for you,

397
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:28,233
your dad and I.

398
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:32,900
[WAILING]

399
00:21:33,033 --> 00:21:35,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:21:46,167 --> 00:21:55,300
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WAILING]

401
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:58,367
[WAILING CONTINUES]

402
00:22:04,067 --> 00:22:06,167
[SOBBING]

403
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:10,733
I feel so sorry for you, Marj.

404
00:22:10,867 --> 00:22:13,233
Do you want me to stay here
with you for now?

405
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:16,000
I'll take care of you.

406
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:17,900
Thank you, Jobert.

407
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:21,167
Marj...

408
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:26,300
thank goodness
you weren't seriously hurt.

409
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:29,767
I couldn't handle it
if I lost you.

410
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:34,567
To be honest, Mom,
when the building collapsed,

411
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,333
I was terrified.

412
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:41,900
I wasn't afraid of the
possibility that I might die...

413
00:22:42,033 --> 00:22:45,067
I was terrified that I might
never see you again.

414
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:48,100
Especially my husband and child.

415
00:22:50,267 --> 00:22:52,933
Now that Thea and Aldrin
are gone,

416
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:54,800
you can finally
have peace, Marj.

417
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:58,533
Aunt Thea is gone?

418
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,600
Yes, Jobert.

419
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:04,000
She's gone.

420
00:23:05,267 --> 00:23:07,233
I still feel guilty.

421
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:10,833
Despite everything she did wrong

422
00:23:10,967 --> 00:23:14,567
and how many times
she tried to kill us,

423
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:18,067
my heart still can't accept
that I couldn't save her.

424
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,600
You shouldn't feel guilty.

425
00:23:20,733 --> 00:23:22,967
It wasn't your fault.

426
00:23:23,133 --> 00:23:26,200
Karma made the decision.

427
00:23:26,333 --> 00:23:27,867
Maybe that's for the best,

428
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:32,933
so justice could finally
be served for Edward's death.

429
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:36,133
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

430
00:23:46,333 --> 00:23:48,500
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

431
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:50,967
[LAUGHTER]

432
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:53,000
- Mom.
- Yes?

433
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:55,000
I thought you were going on
a cruise to fix your marriage?

434
00:23:55,167 --> 00:23:57,200
Why are Weng and Cheche
coming along?

435
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:59,267
Well, we need help
around the ship,

436
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:02,867
and I can't take care
of your father alone.

437
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:05,400
The way you talk, it sounds like
I'm so hard to take care of.

438
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:06,667
Well, it's true.

439
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,067
At least we have company.

440
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,733
- And with a hat, too.
- Hey!

441
00:24:09,867 --> 00:24:12,533
- [LAUGHTER]
- At least Weng gets a vacation.

442
00:24:12,667 --> 00:24:14,200
They look excited.

443
00:24:14,333 --> 00:24:15,367
I'm so excited!

444
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,967
Actually, we're all so excited,
Ma'am Marj!

445
00:24:18,100 --> 00:24:18,967
Ma'am Marj, did you see?

446
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:21,333
Ma'am Regina took us shopping.

447
00:24:21,467 --> 00:24:22,433
Look at that!

448
00:24:22,567 --> 00:24:25,300
- [LAUGHTER]
- Must be nice.

449
00:24:25,433 --> 00:24:28,767
Don't worry,
we'll have a vacation too.

450
00:24:28,933 --> 00:24:31,633
[LAUGHS]

451
00:24:31,767 --> 00:24:33,700
What about you? Are you really

452
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:36,367
going through
with your plan to...

453
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:38,700
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

454
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:40,333
You can stay longer.

455
00:24:40,467 --> 00:24:42,433
No one is asking you to leave.

456
00:24:43,533 --> 00:24:46,567
Don't worry, Dad,
we won't leave right away.

457
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:48,167
But...

458
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:52,133
the sooner we can start over
in a new place,

459
00:24:52,267 --> 00:24:54,367
the sooner we can heal.

460
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:56,300
Especially Ashley.

461
00:24:58,100 --> 00:25:01,067
This house has too many sad
memories for us.

462
00:25:02,267 --> 00:25:07,733
We need a fresh start
for Paolo and the kids.

463
00:25:07,867 --> 00:25:09,333
Including a new home.

464
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:10,567
I get it.

465
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:14,067
But anytime, you can always
come back to visit.

466
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,300
You're always welcome.

467
00:25:16,433 --> 00:25:20,867
But for now, enjoy this house
while yours is being built.

468
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,533
Yes.

469
00:25:22,667 --> 00:25:23,800
Let's go, we'll take you there.

470
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:25,933
Oh, my God! Let's go!

471
00:25:26,067 --> 00:25:27,133
Come on!

472
00:25:27,267 --> 00:25:28,833
[LAUGHS]

473
00:25:28,967 --> 00:25:31,600
My gosh.

474
00:25:31,733 --> 00:25:34,100
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

475
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:37,433
[LIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

476
00:25:40,733 --> 00:25:41,733
Do you girls like it?

477
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:45,867
Like what, Dad?

478
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,700
There's nothing here.

479
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:52,367
This is where we'll build
our dream house.

480
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:54,433
The living room
will be over here,

481
00:25:54,567 --> 00:25:56,100
and the kitchen
will be over there.

482
00:25:57,633 --> 00:26:00,567
Mom, I want my bedroom t
o be here.

483
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,933
And I'll be here
so we're next to each other.

484
00:26:03,067 --> 00:26:04,067
Careful.

485
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,433
[CHUCKLES]

486
00:26:05,567 --> 00:26:06,867
It's beautiful.

487
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,233
[PHONE RINGING]

488
00:26:11,567 --> 00:26:13,367
Hello, Jobert! Hi!

489
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:14,833
- Hello!
- Hi, Mom!

490
00:26:14,967 --> 00:26:17,133
Look, Mom, how beautiful
this place is.

491
00:26:17,267 --> 00:26:19,600
Marj, let me see.

492
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,867
Wow, Marj.

493
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:29,000
Your house actually has
a really beautiful view, Marj.

494
00:26:29,133 --> 00:26:31,200
Our house.

495
00:26:31,333 --> 00:26:33,400
What, Marj?

496
00:26:33,533 --> 00:26:36,900
Our dream house, Marj?

497
00:26:37,033 --> 00:26:39,700
Yes, didn't I promise you
this before?

498
00:26:39,833 --> 00:26:42,733
Well, here it is, our plan
is finally happening.

499
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:44,033
At last, I can finally give you

500
00:26:44,167 --> 00:26:46,867
the dream house
I promised back then.

501
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:49,367
[APPLAUDING]

502
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:50,667
Marj.

503
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,367
Marj, thank you.

504
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:54,433
Thank you, Marj.

505
00:26:54,567 --> 00:26:56,000
You're welcome, Jobert.

506
00:26:56,133 --> 00:26:58,600
Mom, let's just meet at dinner
later.

507
00:26:59,633 --> 00:27:00,967
Take care.

508
00:27:02,633 --> 00:27:04,133
It's beautiful.

509
00:27:04,267 --> 00:27:07,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

510
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:16,000
Are you happy with where
our new house will be built?

511
00:27:17,433 --> 00:27:18,600
Yes, Love.

512
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:22,067
After everything
we've been through

513
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:23,633
and everything we've learned,

514
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:26,733
I know we'll be stronger.

515
00:27:26,867 --> 00:27:29,800
This won't be a house of lies,

516
00:27:29,933 --> 00:27:33,567
jealousy, conflict, and secrets.

517
00:27:35,233 --> 00:27:37,867
This is not just a dream house.

518
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,967
It's a house of second chances.

519
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:43,700
And we'll fill it with love.

520
00:27:46,533 --> 00:27:53,367
["KATOTOHANAN"
BY JESSICA VILLARUBIN PLAYING]

521
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:05,200
["KATOTOHANAN" THEME MUSIC
CONTINUES]
